  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n\r\n  \r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">LIGHT<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A pure spectrum can be produced using a triangular prism-two converging lenses and a narrow slit of white light. The emergent rays are then focused on another converging lens to produce parallel of different colours on the screen at its focus. This produces a spectrum which does not overlap.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Visible light (white light) is a collection of colour component which are; Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, Indigo, Violet (ROYGBIV).<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Dispersion is due to the fact that the different colours of white light travel at different speeds through the glass and therefore, each colour is refracted at a slightly different direction. Red light is deviated least and therefore travels in glass with the greatest speed while violet is the most deviated with the least speed through glass.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Dispersion of White Light By A Glass Prism. When a ray of white light (sunlight) enters a glass prism (denser medium). It emerges out and broken into seven colours. Different colors of light have different frequencies, which causes them to travel at different speeds when they move through matter<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Refractive index =&nbsp;<\/span><img src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAFAAAAAcCAYAAAD2izi6AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAAcLSURBVGhD7ZkHaFVJFIaDxhZ7iQYVoyEq9hpRBLEG0RgbIvaKoCJWDFFRbIi9G6Im9t67BhUs2DF2xd5QE3tJ7J71O+\/O45p9u2vuWzarvA\/Cm5k7d+7Mf8+c9+aPn\/jwhgCfgN6R8QKmpKTI27dvrZpnPnz4oH2+fftmtXjH+\/fv\/63xMl7AIUOGSMGCBa2aZ9avXy9Zs2b9R6H\/Dvu9K1askICAAPny5YvV4piMF3DXrl0ye\/Zsq+aZd+\/eSY0aNaxa+lmzZo1s27bNqoncv39fWrVqZdW8wpmAnz59kqlTp8rw4cMlKSlJoqOjJT4+3n0tKipK2+Li4rQNLl68KAMHDpQRI0bIhAkT3BFRu3ZtefTokZbtsG3HjRsnY8aMkX79+v0gMtcGDBigz9++fbsKPHnyZJk0aZLcvXtXxo4dK+PHj9ctOmPGDPHz85ORI0fKnDlz9P61a9dq+\/z586Vr166aRhziTMDU1FT9y549u+zevVtzCkIiXr58+eTevXvaL0uWLPp58uRJjSCuc61MmTLaDkFBQXq\/nc+fP0vZsmXl3LlzWm\/atKmcPXtWy4iXOXNmefXqlQpfpUoVLfNCcufOLYcPH9Z+JUuWlOTkZC37+\/vrpwHR+vfvr\/Nh7MTEROtKunG+hW\/fvi21atWyai569eolo0ePloSEBKlatars3btX2wsUKKDbBvbv3695D16\/fi3lypXTsp0jR45Is2bNrJpI+fLlNcqgZs2asmTJEtmxY4dUqlRJjh8\/ru3Hjh2Ttm3bahlKlCghz58\/l2fPnklYWJjVKvL161fNuealhYSE6Dwc4lzAdevW6Ray06hRIzl16pQu1iTojx8\/St68ebUMdevW1agFtnhsbKyW7cTExOiWBIRiXEPRokXl6dOnuu2IIANbduXKlVomourUqaNl0sDmzZu1DLdu3ZL69etrmSBo3Lixlh3iXMAWLVrI5cuXrZqLVatWyeDBg+XgwYNSrVo1q1U0Ujdu3CgTJ06Ujh07yvTp02XRokW66JkzZ\/4QbYAACE1e3bRpk9SrV0+j2+Q68hfRbRcWwRibLwu2LykGyIe9e\/eWvn37ah2Ryc9A1LZr106\/UEgNDnAu4P8Jtmn16tWt2n\/K7yEgObN169ZOo8gbfg8BMxCfgF4S8P03pp\/+0PT9OfrzRaCX+AT0Ep+AXvJrCvgzP1dOnDghOXPmlDdv3lgt6QMjglOU4fTp05IpUya5c+eO1aL8egJyhsWw+BkCAwMde36XLl2SiIgIq+YSlPN1GlwCchEXgyMWB3UMRya6Z88ePUtyKN+wYYMexeh76NAhGTVqlB7Cd+7cqZYTjgjw1pYuXSpz585VI5Tj3ePHj3XcLVu2yI0bN3RMJgjYTwsWLFCbC8PhyZMnej\/Pu379usyaNUv27dunfa9evSrFihXTo9+8efO0zQ4uDkc\/rC+e26RJE+uKK2pXr1